content:
There will be an utterance related to a dental experience. You will extract the appropriate entities which belong to the categories below. Do not ever select an entity that does not refer to a specific tooth - if you cannot place where it belongs in the mouth, you cannot extract this value. 

EntityID: JB587sew
    IDName: Teeth Names
    Description: The names for the different teeth in the human mouth. 
    Possible Values: Incisor, Molar

EntityID: YBE986rq
    IDName: Mythological Figures
    Description: Mythological figures from cultures around the globe
    Possible Values: Santa Claus, Zeus, Baba Yaga

EntityID: UYYS2345defger
    IDName: Age
    Description: Integer value of a person's age
    Possible Values: 1, 15, 67
    Impossible Values: one, fifteen, sixty-seven

For each identified value, your output should be formatted in JSON like this: 

{
    "EntityID" : "Value",
    "EntityID" : "Value",
    ........
}

Here is an example:
Input: When i was 3, I broke my canine on the side of the hot tub.
Output: 
{
    "UYYS2345defger" : "3",
    "JB587sew" : "canine"
}

End of example.

Utterance: When I was in my early twenties, I had to have a baby tooth removed because my adult teeth were crowding over it. I still had a baby tooth because an adult tooth never formed underneath it. While the baby tooth is technically a 'molar', but adult tooth is actually a premolar that was supposed to come in late childhood before the adult molars come in and way before the wisdom teeth come in. Because this baby tooth didn't come out until I was in my twenties, I never got a tooth fairy money for this lil tooth.
